odd.head: Appendix IV: Bibliography of compositions by John Duke

list.head: Songs
list.item: 265 Catalogued songs, 1920-84 (see Appendix I for list)
"Music, When Soft Voices Die" (Percy Bysshe Shelley), n.d.
"Softly, Softly the Snow Drifts Down" (Caroline Neilson), 1928
"A Christmas Hymn" (Richard Wilbur) version for solo voice and piano, 1973
"I Love the Lord" for voice and piano, c. 1960
"Magnificat" for solo voice or unison chorus and organ, 1961
"The Way, The Truth, The Life" for voice and organ, c. 1960

list.head: Choral Works
list.item: "The Cloud" (Sara Teasdale) for 3-part women's chorus and piano, n.d.
"Love Unconquerable" (from Antigone by Sophocles) for 4-part women's chorus, n.d.
"Pole Star for This Year" (Archibald MacLeish) for a capella 4-part chorus, n d. (SSAATB)
"Three River Songs" (texts from the Chinese) for 3-part women's chorus and piano, 1963 (SSA)
"When Slim Sophia Mounts Her Horse" (Walter de la Mare) version for 3-part women's chorus, 1981 (SSA)
"A Christman Hymn" (Richard Wilbur) for mixed chorus, 1973 (SATB)
"A Grace Before Singing" for 4-part women's chorus, n.d. (SSAA)
"Magnificat" for solo voice or unison chorus and organ, 1961
"O, Sing Unto the Lord a New Song" for 3-part women's chorus and string orchestra (or organ), 1955, written for the dedication of the Helen Hills Hills Chapel, Smith College (SSA)
"Psalm 23" for treble chorus, 1953, written for the choir of the Class of 1953 (SSAA)

list.head: Symphonic Works
list.item: "Dance in A-major" for string orchestra, n.d.
"The Fairy Glen" for flute, harp and strings, n.d.

list.head: Dramatic Works
list.item: "The Cat That Walked by Himself," a musical fantasy for children, 1944

list.head: Solo Pieces and Chamber Music
list.item: "Air in F-major" for violin and piano, 1942
"Fantasy in A-minor" for violin and piano, 1936
"Melody in E-flat major" for viola and piano, 1946
"Melody in E-flat major" for cello and piano, 1946
"Trio in D-major" for violin, cello, and piano, 1943
"Trio in G-major" for violin, viola, and cello, 1937
"Three Songs in Praise of Death for Voice and String Quartet" (Walt Whitman), song catalog nos. 18-20

list.head: Miscellaneous
list.item: "A Round for Robert," 1973, written for Robert Miller's birthday
"Ave Gertrudia Smithiensis," 1971, written for Gertrude Smith's retirement party
Cadenzas for "Piano Concerto in G-major" by Ludwig van Beethoven, n.d.
Incidental music for "Androcles and the Lion," a marionette play staged by Oliver Larkin, 1952
"Lord, Bless This Food," n.d., written for the Seagle Colony

list.head: Music for Smith College Faculty shows
list.item: "A Day on The Campus" for miscellaneous percussion, 1949. Inscribed: "Affectionately dedicated to Lorraine the Crane"
"Twang the Lyre for Sophia" from Rosina the White Rose of Northampton, 1953
